RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 67. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AWESOME PRINCE chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, challenged from the two path coming around the turn and drew off in the stretch. UNXPECTED TIGER trailed the field through the opening quarter of a mile, came around the turn in the two path, began a bid approaching the quarter pole and gained ground late. SEAX raced off the pace up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the turn and kept on to the finish, no match for the winner. FAST FIXER led the way on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and faded in the lane. MIND FLAYER tracked the pace setter on the outside in the early going, began to drop back while racing in the three path around the turn and continued to tire in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 2 7F Dirt CR: 71. Claiming Purse 20500. FOR FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of Three Races Allowed 2 lbs. Two Races Allowed 4 lbs. HAPPY UNION trailed the field on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn, began a bid passing the quarter pole and improved position in the stretch. CHILD PROOF stalked the leader on the inside up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the turn, veered in and bumped with DA JOURNEYGIRL entering the stretch and was outfinished in the final furlong. WAITWAITDONTTELLME raced in the middle of the pack early, came around the bend in the three and four path, began a bid approaching the quarter pole and gained ground mildly in the lane while never threatening. DA JOURNEYGIRL led the way up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the turn was bumped lightly by CHILD PROOF in upper stretch and weakened from there. SUMMER NITRO raced off the pace on the outside through the early going, continued around the turn in the three path and was not a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 3 1 3/8M Turf CR: 86. Maiden Special Weight Purse 27000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. (Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Not Started For Less Than $25,000. The Same Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Started For Less Than $25,000 And Since Then Have Finished 2nd Or 3rd For $25,000 Or More.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOSQUE REDONDO bumped with the horse his outside at the start, saved ground in the middle of the pack through the opening mile, began a bid headed into the third turn, dueled on the inside around that bend and continued to battle to the wire to just get the win. TYPHOON LAGOON bumped with the horse to his inside leaving the gate, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside around the first turn and the first time down the stretch, raced in the two path around the second turn, challenged from the two path coming around the final bend and dueled to the wire to just miss. PICCADILLY trailed the field on the inside the first time by the stands, saved ground around the second turn, began to move up from the rail coming up the backstretch and around the far turn and continued to improve position in the lane. BASSANIO (GB) saved ground around the first turn, raced off the pace on the inside through the next three quarters of a mile, began a bid coming from the two path coming around the last bend and finished evenly. UNEXPECTED (JPN) brushed with the horse to his inside at the break, raced off the pace on the outside in the early going, saved ground headed into the far turn and made no bid. GRAPHENE CASSOCK chased the leader from the three path around the first turn and down the stretch, continued around the second bend still in the three path, dropped back while saving ground around the third turn and was empty in the lane. KYLE'S DEGREE brushed with the horse to his outside at the start, recovered to lead the field on the inside the first time by and around the clubhouse turn, dropped back after a mile had been run, came around the final turn wide, continued to tire in the stretch and was vanned off.
